FBIS3-25732 "drafr039_e_94004" FBIS-AFR-94-039 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Feb 1994 WEST AFRICA Nigeria Government Said Trying To Maintain Peace With Cameroon AB2702173094 Kaduna Radio Nigeria in English 1700 GMT 27 Feb 94 AB2702173094 Kaduna Radio Nigeria Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The minister of external affairs, Alhaji Babagana Kingibe, will brief the nation early next week on the Nigeria- Cameroon border issue. The minister of information and culture, Professor Jerry Gana, who made this known on Radio Link, said the Federal Government was aware of the dangers of allowing the conflict to escalate. He explained that the government was doing everything possible to maintain peace and to ensure that the situation did not degenerate into war.
